Lab Setup: Ubuntu Server 24.04 Bare Metal AI Workstation


AI Server Components
1. NVIDIA RTX 2080 Super GPU
2. Ollama (LLM inference engine)
3. Open WebUI (browser interface)
4. Qwen 2.5 8B model
5. Docker containers
6. Tailscale remote access
7. Automatic idle suspend
8. Wake-on-LAN support


------------------------------------------------------------

HARDWARE PLATFORM

GPU:
	NVIDIA RTX 2080 Super

Deployment Type:
	Bare metal Ubuntu server

Access:
	LAN + Tailscale

Power Management:
	Suspend after 15 minutes of inactivity
	Wake-on-LAN enabled


------------------------------------------------------------

OPERATING SYSTEM SETUP

Install Ubuntu Server 24.04 normally.

After installation update the system:

	sudo apt update
	sudo apt upgrade -y


------------------------------------------------------------

VERIFY GPU DETECTION

Check that the system detects the NVIDIA GPU:

	lspci | grep -i nvidia

You should see the RTX 2080 Super listed.


------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL NVIDIA DRIVERS

Install recommended drivers automatically:

	sudo ubuntu-drivers autoinstall

Reboot the system:

	sudo reboot


------------------------------------------------------------

VERIFY GPU DRIVER

After reboot run:

	nvidia-smi

Expected output should display:

	GPU name
	driver version
	memory usage


------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL OLLAMA

Install Ollama using the official installer:

	curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh

Verify installation:

	ollama --version


------------------------------------------------------------

ENABLE OLLAMA SERVICE

Enable the Ollama system service:

	sudo systemctl enable ollama
	sudo systemctl start ollama

Verify service status:

	sudo systemctl status ollama


------------------------------------------------------------

TEST OLLAMA API

Ollama exposes an API on port 11434.

Test locally:

	curl http://localhost:11434

You should receive a response confirming the server is running.


------------------------------------------------------------

DOWNLOAD AN 8B MODEL

Pull the Qwen 2.5 8B model:

	ollama pull qwen2.5:8b

Test the model:

	ollama run qwen2.5:8b

You can now interact with the model via the terminal.


------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL DOCKER

Open WebUI will run inside Docker.

Install Docker:

	sudo apt install docker.io docker-compose-plugin -y

Enable Docker service:

	sudo systemctl enable docker
	sudo systemctl start docker

Add user to Docker group:

	sudo usermod -aG docker $USER

Apply group changes:

	newgrp docker


------------------------------------------------------------

VERIFY DOCKER INSTALLATION

Run the Docker test container:

	docker run hello-world


------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL OPEN WEBUI

Create WebUI directory:

	mkdir ~/open-webui
	cd ~/open-webui


------------------------------------------------------------

CREATE DOCKER COMPOSE FILE

Create compose configuration:

	nano docker-compose.yaml

Paste the following configuration:

	version: "3"

	services:
	  open-webui:
	    image: ghcr.io/open-webui/open-webui:main
	    container_name: open-webui
	    ports:
	      - "3000:8080"
	    volumes:
	      - open-webui:/app/backend/data
	    environment:
	      - OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434
	    restart: unless-stopped

	volumes:
	  open-webui:


------------------------------------------------------------

START OPEN WEBUI

Start the container:

	docker compose up -d

Verify container status:

	docker compose ps


------------------------------------------------------------

ACCESS WEBUI

Open a browser on the LAN:

	http://SERVER-IP:3000

Create a user account in the interface.

Connect the Ollama endpoint:

	http://SERVER-IP:11434

You can now run models directly from the browser.


------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL TAILSCALE

Install Tailscale for remote access:

	curl -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh

Start Tailscale:

	sudo tailscale up

The AI server is now reachable through the Tailscale network.


------------------------------------------------------------

ENABLE WAKE-ON-LAN

Install required utility:

	sudo apt install ethtool -y

Check network interface name:

	ip a

Example interface:

	enp3s0


------------------------------------------------------------

VERIFY WOL SUPPORT

Check WOL capability:

	sudo ethtool enp3s0

Look for:

	Wake-on: g


------------------------------------------------------------

ENABLE WOL

Enable Wake-on-LAN:

	sudo ethtool -s enp3s0 wol g


------------------------------------------------------------

MAKE WOL PERSISTENT

Create service:

	sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/wol.service

Paste configuration:

	[Unit]
	Description=Enable Wake-on-LAN

	[Service]
	Type=oneshot
	ExecStart=/sbin/ethtool -s enp3s0 wol g

	[Install]
	WantedBy=multi-user.target

Enable service:

	sudo systemctl enable wol


------------------------------------------------------------

AUTO-SUSPEND WHEN OLLAMA IS IDLE

Create idle monitoring script:

	sudo nano /usr/local/bin/ollama_idle_monitor.sh

Paste the following script:

	#!/bin/bash

	IDLE_LIMIT=900
	OLLAMA_PORT=11434
	last_activity=$(date +%s)

	while true
	do
	    connections=$(ss -tn state established '( sport = :11434 )' | wc -l)

	    if [ "$connections" -gt 1 ]; then
	        last_activity=$(date +%s)
	    fi

	    now=$(date +%s)
	    idle_time=$((now-last_activity))

	    if [ "$idle_time" -gt "$IDLE_LIMIT" ]; then
	        systemctl suspend
	    fi

	    sleep 60
	done

Make script executable:

	sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/ollama_idle_monitor.sh


------------------------------------------------------------

CREATE SYSTEMD SERVICE

Create service file:

	sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/ollama-idle.service

Paste configuration:

	[Unit]
	Description=Ollama Idle Monitor

	[Service]
	ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/ollama_idle_monitor.sh
	Restart=always

	[Install]
	WantedBy=multi-user.target


------------------------------------------------------------

ENABLE SERVICE

Reload systemd:

	sudo systemctl daemon-reload

Enable service:

	sudo systemctl enable ollama-idle

Start service:

	sudo systemctl start ollama-idle


------------------------------------------------------------

VERIFY SYSTEM

1. Open WebUI and run Qwen 8B
2. Confirm GPU usage with:

	nvidia-smi

3. Stop using Ollama for 15 minutes

4. System will automatically suspend

5. Wake system remotely via Wake-on-LAN


